      <bioghist>
         
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         
         <p>Alden holds degrees from Duke University and Colorado College, as well as 
advanced degrees from Indiana University, and the SMU Perkins School of Theology. 
She is currently (1998) Coordinator for Service-Learning for the Kenan Ethics 
Program.</p>
      
      </bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent>
         
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         
         <p>This unprocessed accession is comprised primarily of published materials (magazines, newsletters, and photocopies and clippings of newspaper and magazine articles) and of a few manuscript items related to women's employment, religious, legal, and domestic issues. The papers document Rev. Alden's feminist activism during the 1970s and early 1980s while she was living in Texas. Rev. Alden's folder titles and original arrangement of items were maintained. This collection is open for use.</p>
      
      </scopecontent>
      
